WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=LOCAL:00:00:00.000,MPEGTS:0

00:27.059 --> 00:29.977
["Don't Wanna Be Yours"
by Lady Raven playing]

01:28.116 --> 01:31.419
[girl singing along]

01:38.101 --> 01:40.636
[singing off-key]

01:44.821 --> 01:46.357
-[brakes squealing]
-Go, go, go, Dad.

01:47.240 --> 01:48.776
We're not gonna break
any laws, Riley.

01:48.969 --> 01:50.428
We'll get there when
you wanted to get there.

01:50.581 --> 01:51.772
I promise.

01:52.656 --> 01:53.731
Trust me.

01:54.691 --> 01:56.917
[volume increases]

01:57.110 --> 01:59.875
[resumes singing]

02:00.489 --> 02:02.024
Maybe I'll be a singer.

02:02.216 --> 02:04.214
Yeah, maybe.

02:09.397 --> 02:11.088
[song ends]

02:16.118 --> 02:17.347
Hurry. Come on, come on.

02:17.538 --> 02:19.382
Wait. Wait, wait, wait, wait.
I gotta tie my shoe.

02:19.613 --> 02:21.994
No dad jokes.
This is serious. Come on.

02:22.185 --> 02:22.992
I'm sorry.

02:23.183 --> 02:24.528
[shouts playfully] I'm sorry!

02:27.139 --> 02:28.868
-[dad] Nope. Nope. Nope.
-[Riley] Yes. Yes.

02:29.020 --> 02:30.711
[dad] Nope, nope, nope...

02:31.900 --> 02:33.321
[Riley laughs]
That's unfair. I'm twelve.

02:33.476 --> 02:35.203
-[dad] Champion!
-[Riley] Oh, whatever.

02:36.356 --> 02:38.045
We're late.
This is frustrating, Dad.

02:38.238 --> 02:39.465
We should have come earlier.

02:39.697 --> 02:41.233
Yeah, this was the earliest
I could get off work, Riley.

02:41.424 --> 02:42.537
Sorry.

02:43.920 --> 02:45.034
Come here, come here.

02:45.226 --> 02:47.338
-[excited chatter]
-[muffled music playing]

02:47.569 --> 02:48.529
-Shoulders?
-[Riley] Yeah.

02:49.142 --> 02:51.755
[chatter continues]

02:52.445 --> 02:54.864
[crowd cheering]

02:55.057 --> 02:56.632
[all cheering loudly]

02:57.821 --> 03:01.200
[scattered booing]

03:01.355 --> 03:02.853
[girl in crowd]
Is she coming or what?

03:03.044 --> 03:04.541
[indistinct chatter]

03:05.157 --> 03:06.000
[girl in crowd]
Come out! Come out!

03:06.193 --> 03:08.075
-[door opens]
-[crowd cheers]

03:08.266 --> 03:09.496
[Riley] Whoo!

03:10.456 --> 03:15.178
[cheering intensifies]

03:18.213 --> 03:19.135
[Riley] Put me down.

03:19.902 --> 03:24.203
[cheering continues]

03:25.778 --> 03:27.391
[girl in crowd] Yes, queen!

03:28.389 --> 03:29.656
Slay!

03:32.652 --> 03:33.919
[girl] Lady Raven!

03:34.149 --> 03:35.417
Oh, my God!

03:36.415 --> 03:38.297
[girls together]
She waved at me.

03:40.178 --> 03:41.638
I think I got a good photo.

03:41.791 --> 03:43.441
That was kind of exciting.

03:44.786 --> 03:45.746
[Riley] I'm so happy she added

03:45.977 --> 03:47.819
this afternoon concert
after she sold out.

03:48.779 --> 03:49.817
Tickets,
I got tenth row tickets.

03:49.971 --> 03:51.737
-No thank you.
-Tenth row?

03:51.928 --> 03:54.847
They wouldn't be real, honey.
Don't let people fool you.

03:55.040 --> 03:57.574
-Our seats are good enough.
-We're row 44.

03:57.803 --> 04:00.607
-On the floor! Bam!
-[chuckles]

04:00.838 --> 04:02.374
[indistinct chatter]

04:02.604 --> 04:04.485
[dad] So, give me the update.

04:05.715 --> 04:07.480
What's going on
with those girls at school?

04:07.673 --> 04:08.901
It's fine.

04:09.133 --> 04:10.054
It's fine?

04:10.245 --> 04:11.360
I don't really
wanna talk about it.

04:13.740 --> 04:16.006
Okay. Come here.

04:16.198 --> 04:17.503
[kisses]

04:17.658 --> 04:18.809
You.

04:20.000 --> 04:22.380
[fans chattering]

04:27.719 --> 04:30.368
["Save Me" by Lady Raven
playing over speakers]

04:30.560 --> 04:32.864
[excited, overlapping chatter]

04:42.273 --> 04:43.156
Dad, look.

04:43.347 --> 04:47.341
["Save Me"
by Lady Raven continues]

04:53.255 --> 04:54.177
Riley.

05:03.162 --> 05:04.468
[dad laughs]

05:04.699 --> 05:06.887
Yeah, baby. Go!

05:18.906 --> 05:21.519
They aren't mean anymore.
They just don't include me.

05:21.710 --> 05:23.554
They keep posting
stuff together.

05:24.782 --> 05:26.049
[dad] I see.

05:26.242 --> 05:28.738
It must be hard seeing what
everyone's doing all the time.

05:30.120 --> 05:32.308
You guys are so connected
even when you're not that close.

05:34.076 --> 05:36.533
Why don't you and I
take a picture together
when we go inside?

05:36.686 --> 05:37.646
You and your dad.

05:37.801 --> 05:39.643
Jody will be so jelly.

05:40.142 --> 05:40.949
[scoffs]

05:41.180 --> 05:42.830
That would be
like the worst idea.

05:43.022 --> 05:44.559
And don't say jelly, Dad.

05:45.326 --> 05:46.633
[stammers, sighs]

05:46.786 --> 05:49.666
[up-tempo music
playing over speakers]

06:02.416 --> 06:05.257
[hip-hop music
playing over speakers]

06:09.635 --> 06:10.979
[Riley] These seats slap, Dad.

06:11.132 --> 06:12.400
Thank you. Thank you.

06:12.554 --> 06:14.549
This is literally
the best day of my life!

06:14.742 --> 06:17.506
You did this. Four A's and a B.
I told you I'd get it for you.

06:17.661 --> 06:19.082
I never got grades like that.

06:19.235 --> 06:20.579
[Riley exhales happily]

06:20.770 --> 06:22.154
A deal's a deal.

06:22.306 --> 06:23.727
I did get lucky with these
seats though, didn't I?

06:23.882 --> 06:25.034
I know, I know.

06:25.647 --> 06:26.531
Meant to be.

06:26.762 --> 06:29.027
We are Papa's Boots.

06:29.220 --> 06:32.983
-[scattered cheers]
-[upbeat R&amp;B music playing]

06:49.495 --> 06:52.912
[music continues]

06:53.104 --> 06:54.986
[people cheering]

07:04.932 --> 07:07.121
So, what does "crispy" mean?

07:07.312 --> 07:08.657
It means something is good.

07:08.887 --> 07:09.925
Use it in a sentence.

07:10.692 --> 07:12.765
Dude, your house is crispy.

07:13.572 --> 07:14.570
I see.

07:15.877 --> 07:18.795
So if I were to come
to somebody's house and say,

07:18.948 --> 07:21.599
"Yo, your house is extra fried."

07:21.828 --> 07:22.904
Don't ever say that.

07:23.134 --> 07:24.440
Why? Extra fried is better
than crispy.

07:24.631 --> 07:27.397
Stop. I'm not teaching you
any more words.

07:29.356 --> 07:33.310
[crowd cheering]

07:37.343 --> 07:40.030
Whoo-hoo! Whoo!

07:42.796 --> 07:44.716
[cheering continues]

07:46.289 --> 07:48.902
[girls screaming]

07:50.284 --> 07:52.088
[Lady Raven] How y'all doing,
my queens and kings?

07:52.281 --> 07:53.663
[cheers and applause]

07:53.817 --> 07:55.314
Oh, my God!

07:56.044 --> 07:58.502
[cheering continues]

07:58.693 --> 08:01.151
[melodic keyboard
and bass playing]

08:10.598 --> 08:13.593
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

08:17.509 --> 08:20.698
[Lady Raven performing
"Care for You"]

08:22.194 --> 08:25.228
Oh, my God. Oh, my God! Yes!

08:28.415 --> 08:30.988
[crowd singing along]

08:51.918 --> 08:54.798
[crowd cheering]

08:59.175 --> 09:01.441
[thunder booms]

09:02.976 --> 09:06.432
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Care for You"]

09:08.429 --> 09:11.080
[crowd singing along]

09:18.683 --> 09:21.064
Hey, I gotta go to the bathroom.

09:21.217 --> 09:22.408
You can either stay in the seat

09:22.600 --> 09:23.983
or you can come with me
and wait outside the men's room.

09:24.174 --> 09:25.903
I'm good, Dad.
I don't wanna leave.

09:26.708 --> 09:27.900
You stay in the seat.

09:28.091 --> 09:29.895
-Promise?
-I promise.

09:30.319 --> 09:31.969
Riley, I mean it.

09:32.200 --> 09:33.967
I'm good, Dad.
I don't want to leave.

09:39.035 --> 09:42.146
[song continues, muffled]

09:42.300 --> 09:44.257
[toilet flushes]

09:51.747 --> 09:52.783
[lock clicks]

10:01.192 --> 10:04.880
[man panting, frightened]

10:12.521 --> 10:14.480
[grunting]

10:16.553 --> 10:19.203
[frightened panting continues]

10:31.722 --> 10:33.565
[tires screeching]

10:41.091 --> 10:43.011
[water running]

11:05.131 --> 11:06.629
[indistinct chatter]

11:06.820 --> 11:08.549
[woman] Oh, hey! Cooper!

11:09.163 --> 11:11.505
Hi. You're here with Riley?

11:12.273 --> 11:13.079
Yep.

11:13.271 --> 11:14.923
[singsong] I'm here with Jody.

11:15.806 --> 11:17.189
-[dry chuckle]
-I haven't, uh...

11:17.342 --> 11:19.685
haven't seen you since
that whole parent-teacher...

11:19.914 --> 11:21.911
...thing. [awkward laugh]

11:22.104 --> 11:22.987
It's good to see you.

11:23.178 --> 11:25.368
Yeah.
Listen, I just really do hope

11:25.559 --> 11:27.903
that they can be friends still,
you know?

11:28.824 --> 11:29.823
You know how girls are
at this age.

11:30.014 --> 11:31.167
[gags, laughs]

11:31.358 --> 11:33.087
And I talked to Jody
and she's gonna work real hard

11:33.278 --> 11:34.737
to include Riley
in things, so...

11:35.583 --> 11:37.349
Riley was really hurt
by all this.

11:37.503 --> 11:39.807
As a dad, it's hard to see that.

11:40.306 --> 11:41.496
Right.

11:43.377 --> 11:44.492
I gotta get back to the seat.

11:44.684 --> 11:46.795
Okay. Well, just tell her
that Jody and Sarah and Sarah C.

11:46.950 --> 11:50.136
are sitting right there
in section 107,
and they'd love to see her.

11:51.096 --> 11:51.903
I'll see you soon.

11:52.555 --> 11:53.554
Yeah, good to see you.

12:12.025 --> 12:15.020
[engines revving]

12:15.251 --> 12:17.171
[tires screeching]

12:18.937 --> 12:20.818
[crowd cheering]

12:23.469 --> 12:24.697
Hi.

12:26.311 --> 12:27.999
Jody and her mom are here.

12:28.231 --> 12:29.191
Where?

12:30.035 --> 12:31.149
Not near us.

12:31.916 --> 12:33.031
Forget about them.

12:34.912 --> 12:37.293
[Lady Raven]
My father left when I was seven.

12:38.253 --> 12:40.518
I held that anger
for a long time.

12:41.440 --> 12:42.669
It was who I was.

12:43.897 --> 12:47.815
And then one day,
I decided I had to forgive him,

12:48.046 --> 12:49.504
or I would never move on.

12:50.810 --> 12:53.920
I pretended like
he was in front of me,
and I said,

12:54.842 --> 12:57.531
"You are not responsible
for hurting me.

12:58.222 --> 12:59.297
I release you."

13:00.372 --> 13:01.869
Everything got better
after that.

13:02.024 --> 13:05.249
[cheers and applause]

13:05.440 --> 13:07.976
I want you to picture
someone who hurt you.

13:08.936 --> 13:10.971
I want you to try
to forgive them.

13:11.125 --> 13:13.197
Say to yourself,
"I release you."

13:13.966 --> 13:16.578
And if you feel you have,

13:16.731 --> 13:19.342
I want you to turn on the light
on your phones.

13:42.421 --> 13:45.070
[playing gentle melody on piano]

13:51.215 --> 13:54.326
["Release"
by Lady Raven playing]

14:05.424 --> 14:08.994
[crowd singing along]

14:35.107 --> 14:37.066
[song continues]

14:50.237 --> 14:53.040
[crowd singing along]

15:10.512 --> 15:12.933
[Riley] We have to hurry
while they set up
the stage for the next song.

15:13.777 --> 15:14.699
-Hi.
-[vendor] Hi.

15:14.891 --> 15:16.157
Um, can I get that
in a small, please?

15:16.388 --> 15:17.885
Uh, I want that too.

15:18.077 --> 15:19.768
Umm... [clicks tongue]

15:20.765 --> 15:22.071
Look,
I only have one left, ladies.

15:22.302 --> 15:24.759
I was standing here before her.
Like, forever.

15:26.104 --> 15:28.139
It's okay, Riley,
let her have it.
She really wants it.

15:28.331 --> 15:29.751
We can find another one later.

15:30.827 --> 15:31.633
-Yeah?
-Sure, Dad.

15:31.826 --> 15:33.055
Okay.

15:35.820 --> 15:38.238
You guys are good family.
Good values and stuff.

15:38.468 --> 15:39.890
Trust me, you don't see that.

15:40.043 --> 15:43.346
Listen. I'll get more soon.
I'll put one for you aside.

15:43.538 --> 15:46.226
Just come see me in like...
ten minutes. All right?

15:47.953 --> 15:49.720
-Okay.
-All right.

15:49.912 --> 15:51.142
[crowd cheers in distance]

15:51.334 --> 15:53.254
[indistinct chatter]

15:56.325 --> 15:57.285
Psst!

15:59.091 --> 16:00.627
-Cooper.
-Jamie.

16:00.819 --> 16:02.547
Hey, what's with
all the police trucks outside

16:02.739 --> 16:04.159
and the cameras everywhere,
Jamie?

16:04.389 --> 16:05.388
Something happening?

16:08.268 --> 16:10.956
I'm not supposed to tell.
Don't rat me out.

16:11.456 --> 16:12.147
I won't.

16:13.491 --> 16:15.602
You know the Butcher? Hmm?

16:15.756 --> 16:18.559
That frickin' nutjob
that goes around
just chopping people up?

16:20.479 --> 16:21.709
Yeah.

16:21.901 --> 16:24.973
Well, the feds or whatever heard
that he's gonna be here today.

16:25.779 --> 16:27.930
So they set up a trap for him.

16:28.082 --> 16:30.541
This whole concert, it's a trap.

16:30.771 --> 16:32.230
Wow. Here?

16:32.384 --> 16:34.726
Yeah. Yeah, they're
watching all the exits.

16:34.956 --> 16:36.570
They're checking everyone
that leaves.

16:36.723 --> 16:38.989
There's no way
to get out of here,
except backstage, I guess.

16:39.181 --> 16:40.870
But no one can get backstage.

16:41.025 --> 16:42.829
[both chuckle]

16:43.021 --> 16:44.865
Yeah. See?

16:45.018 --> 16:46.055
It's kinda dope, right?

16:46.246 --> 16:47.590
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

16:48.974 --> 16:50.663
Don't tell anyone. I'll get--
I'll get in deep crap.

16:50.855 --> 16:51.892
No.

16:52.775 --> 16:54.465
Okay... Uh, I gotta get back.

16:54.618 --> 16:55.732
But come see me
for that T-shirt.

16:56.308 --> 16:57.958
-For sure, Jamie.
-[Jamie chuckles]

17:02.145 --> 17:04.104
[Cooper] I just heard
about this funnel cake stand.

17:04.296 --> 17:05.485
I think it's down here.

17:05.715 --> 17:07.099
I'm kinda craving it.

17:07.674 --> 17:08.595
Hold on.

17:09.748 --> 17:10.670
Let me think about where it is
for a second.

17:10.862 --> 17:11.822
[electronic beep]

17:12.053 --> 17:13.934
Come on, Dad.
It's not good for you anyway.

17:18.811 --> 17:21.114
Actually, you know what?
I think it was further back
where we were.

17:21.346 --> 17:22.344
Do you mind?

17:26.798 --> 17:28.794
[Riley]
She started the next song.
Let's get back to our seats.

17:29.026 --> 17:30.255
[Cooper] Ugh...

17:31.099 --> 17:32.251
I thought this was it.

17:32.443 --> 17:33.556
Dad, come on.

17:56.443 --> 17:57.480
[woman grunts, gasps]

17:58.286 --> 17:59.323
[scattered screams]

17:59.515 --> 18:00.745
[officer]
We got a patron injury.

18:00.899 --> 18:02.242
-[Riley] What happened?
-[Cooper sighs]

18:02.472 --> 18:04.700
I think that woman drank
too much, lost her balance.

18:06.197 --> 18:07.925
Let's clear out
and give her some space.

18:11.765 --> 18:13.916
Hey. Why don't we go outside
for a second?

18:14.147 --> 18:15.337
Then we can go back in.

18:15.528 --> 18:17.872
Why? What's going on, Dad?

18:22.902 --> 18:24.707
[indistinct radio chatter]

18:25.513 --> 18:26.858
[Lady Raven singing, muffled]

18:27.087 --> 18:28.969
Wait, isn't this
one of the songs
you always play?

18:29.199 --> 18:30.659
Mm-hm.

18:30.813 --> 18:33.386
Well, let's stop
messing around out here
and get back to our seats.

18:33.578 --> 18:35.036
[indistinct radio chatter]

18:35.268 --> 18:36.420
-[laughs] Okay.
-Come on.

18:37.801 --> 18:40.643
[Lady Raven performs "Liar"]

18:42.065 --> 18:44.023
[crowd cheering]

18:48.246 --> 18:49.553
[Riley] Whoo!

18:52.009 --> 18:54.198
[song ends]

18:54.353 --> 18:57.579
[cheers and applause]

18:57.770 --> 18:59.651
How you all doing?
You having fun?

18:59.805 --> 19:02.494
-[crowd cheers]
-Whoo! Yeah!

19:02.647 --> 19:07.447
This next song I wrote
with a friend of mine,
Parker Wayne.

19:07.639 --> 19:09.559
[crowd cheers]

19:11.287 --> 19:14.167
Wish I could just
scream his name,
and he'd join me for this song.

19:14.359 --> 19:16.240
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

19:16.394 --> 19:20.312
Hey, maybe if we all scream
his name,

19:20.504 --> 19:21.962
he might hear us.

19:23.230 --> 19:27.378
On three,
everybody scream "Parker!"

19:27.607 --> 19:30.027
One, two, three.

19:30.219 --> 19:32.561
[crowd screaming] Parker!

19:32.715 --> 19:34.712
[crowd cheers]

19:34.943 --> 19:36.478
[mechanism clunks, whirs]

19:37.092 --> 19:38.167
Oh, my God!

19:38.359 --> 19:40.126
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

19:40.318 --> 19:42.200
[echoing thuds]

19:43.468 --> 19:46.884
[crowd cheers]

19:47.115 --> 19:48.421
Oh, my God.

19:48.613 --> 19:50.801
[music begins]

19:55.833 --> 19:58.482
[performing
Lady Raven's "Hiding"]

20:01.438 --> 20:04.511
[crowd singing along]

20:14.342 --> 20:17.299
[Lady Raven singing
with Parker Wayne]

20:31.776 --> 20:33.926
["Hiding" continues]

20:42.183 --> 20:44.180
Look in the stage
where that guy came out.

20:44.371 --> 20:45.446
I wonder what's down there.

20:46.753 --> 20:49.633
Hey, we should climb down
and see where it leads.

20:49.863 --> 20:51.630
It looks really cool.

20:51.783 --> 20:53.049
What?

20:53.203 --> 20:55.200
Wouldn't it be unbelievable
to see what's down there?

20:55.431 --> 20:57.120
See how they put on the show?

20:57.351 --> 20:59.156
There might be costumes
and things.

20:59.348 --> 21:01.383
That's crazy,
we can't go down there.

21:02.343 --> 21:03.419
You're acting strange.

21:03.956 --> 21:05.377
Is something wrong, Dad?

21:06.797 --> 21:07.873
No.

21:08.948 --> 21:10.792
I'm just excited for you,
is all.

21:10.945 --> 21:13.902
[Parker Wayne rapping]

21:15.745 --> 21:17.512
You're right, it's crazy.

21:17.704 --> 21:19.124
Forget your stupid dad.

21:20.084 --> 21:21.197
This concert...

21:22.004 --> 21:23.157
...is crispy.

21:24.155 --> 21:27.035
["Hiding" continues]

21:31.144 --> 21:32.987
[trapdoor mechanism clattering]

21:43.124 --> 21:45.889
I'm gonna go see if
they have that T-shirt for you
back at the stand.

21:46.081 --> 21:47.618
Oh, okay. Thanks, Dad.

21:51.382 --> 21:53.110
[laughing]
Oh, hey! Dad of the year!

21:53.340 --> 21:54.914
Hold one sec. Um... [laughs]

21:55.106 --> 21:58.102
Right. I gotta get you a, uh,
small concert tour tee.

21:58.331 --> 22:00.328
I was about to go down
to the storage closet
to get more merch.

22:00.520 --> 22:01.596
I can walk with you.

22:01.788 --> 22:03.631
Sure, sure, sure.
Um, I'll be right back, Dawn.

22:03.785 --> 22:06.011
You got this, girl.
Just hold it down. All right?

22:07.279 --> 22:08.853
-[electronic beep]
-[lock clicks]

22:11.656 --> 22:12.693
[Jamie]<i> What do you do, Cooper?</i>

22:13.193 --> 22:14.077
Fire department.

22:14.269 --> 22:15.496
[chuckles] No shit!

22:15.688 --> 22:18.147
[sighs] Of course it's
all the way up there.

22:20.412 --> 22:21.679
[Jamie grunting]

22:21.834 --> 22:23.369
Here. Let me help you with that.

22:26.325 --> 22:29.667
[Jamie]
Bro! You're strong. [laughs]

22:30.397 --> 22:31.779
They ever find that guy?

22:32.892 --> 22:33.890
The Butcher?

22:34.082 --> 22:35.964
No, no.
I haven't heard anything lately.

22:36.157 --> 22:38.537
You know,
I'm kind of obsessed with him.

22:38.767 --> 22:40.957
I've been following him
for all 12 victims.

22:41.188 --> 22:42.877
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

22:43.069 --> 22:45.296
[music playing in distance]

22:45.488 --> 22:46.909
You're not squeamish, are you?

22:47.600 --> 22:48.945
Not too bad.

22:51.209 --> 22:53.438
Remember when they found
that woman on the bridge?

22:54.628 --> 22:57.853
Well, one of my boys
was jogging on the bridge

22:58.006 --> 22:59.467
before they covered it up.

23:00.886 --> 23:02.691
That's pieces, dawg.

23:02.883 --> 23:04.420
She's deli-prepped.

23:04.611 --> 23:07.147
Like, this dude
is next-level insane.

23:08.222 --> 23:10.256
Sorry.
I didn't mean to upset you.

23:11.408 --> 23:12.483
We cool?

23:13.482 --> 23:14.558
[chuckling] Yeah.

23:14.789 --> 23:17.130
[laughs] Would be dope
if they caught him today.

23:18.282 --> 23:21.240
We had a training thing.
All the employees of the arena.

23:21.432 --> 23:23.121
They gave us a code to say
in each section of the arena

23:23.275 --> 23:26.194
in case we got stopped
by the police.
Real undercover stuff.

23:26.653 --> 23:27.690
That's kinda cool.

23:27.882 --> 23:29.112
What's your code? I mean...

23:30.417 --> 23:31.839
If you can say. I don't want
you to get into trouble.

23:32.069 --> 23:34.410
[scoffs]
I mean, you're fire department,
Cooper. You're on our side.

23:34.641 --> 23:35.794
Yeah.

23:39.134 --> 23:40.401
[whispers] "Hamilton."

23:41.861 --> 23:43.128
[box cutter clicks]

23:45.356 --> 23:46.699
Can you hold this?

23:46.891 --> 23:49.196
[music continues in distance]

23:49.349 --> 23:51.385
Oh, yeah. Ooh. There you go.

23:55.493 --> 23:56.721
Here, take the top one.

23:57.913 --> 23:59.525
-What do I owe you?
-Ah, don't worry about it.

23:59.756 --> 24:01.406
Pass it forward, as they say.

24:03.365 --> 24:04.978
-Don't forget this.
-[box cutter clicks]

24:05.208 --> 24:06.745
Don't want you to get cut.

24:06.975 --> 24:08.050
Thanks, bro.

24:09.087 --> 24:10.355
[Jamie laughs]

24:10.968 --> 24:12.811
[indistinct chatter]

24:13.042 --> 24:17.075
[music plays in distance]

24:35.084 --> 24:37.466
[muffled chatter]

24:39.194 --> 24:40.308
[male officer]
White, north side.

24:40.499 --> 24:41.612
Red, east side.

24:41.804 --> 24:44.723
Black, south side
and green for the west side.

24:44.877 --> 24:46.220
Our situation:

24:46.451 --> 24:48.448
Let's keep it clear
who we're dealing with.

24:49.331 --> 24:51.174
He is a danger to everyone.

24:51.328 --> 24:53.209
This is a photo
of one of his victims,

24:53.363 --> 24:55.476
a young man who went
to the state university.

24:55.630 --> 24:57.319
He studied to become a teacher.

24:57.550 --> 24:58.816
Married.

24:59.008 --> 25:01.236
Had a two-year-old son.
Took care of his parents.

25:02.925 --> 25:06.075
He was awarded
the "Most Liked Teacher"
at his school where he works.

25:07.188 --> 25:08.878
These are the people
who should win.

25:10.145 --> 25:11.988
Remember what the profiler said.

25:12.218 --> 25:14.561
If we get into a confrontation
with our unsub,

25:14.753 --> 25:16.597
our job is to get him alone,

25:16.789 --> 25:18.900
away from civilians
as quickly as possible.

25:19.130 --> 25:23.661
I will personally take
the team member who brings
this freak down out to dinner.

25:23.853 --> 25:24.660
-Let's go. Get to work.
-[electronic beep]

25:24.890 --> 25:26.120
-[man] There was no trouble?
-No, no.

25:26.350 --> 25:27.655
[male officer]
Let's run down our SMEAC.

25:27.847 --> 25:30.727
Situation, blind spot
on northeast corner
of the stadium...

25:30.959 --> 25:32.264
Sorry, guys.

25:32.417 --> 25:34.991
Just gotta...
check the coffee, okay?

25:35.144 --> 25:36.872
Just...
just gonna squeeze through here.

25:37.026 --> 25:38.984
Jeez. You guys are big. [laughs]

25:39.137 --> 25:39.982
So many of you.

25:40.174 --> 25:41.749
Sorry. [chuckles] Excuse me.

25:41.979 --> 25:43.784
[officer] ...lower two thirds
of the concourse.

25:43.975 --> 25:45.512
[Cooper sighs]

25:46.894 --> 25:49.084
We think our unsub was spotted
on the top concourse.

25:49.276 --> 25:52.117
There is a stairwell
in the southwest corner.
We can use that.

25:52.309 --> 25:53.961
Now, this is my concern.

25:54.191 --> 25:56.725
The safety
of the general public,
the staff...

25:56.918 --> 25:58.876
[continues, indistinct]

26:00.334 --> 26:02.908
[man whispering] Hey. Hey.

26:03.099 --> 26:04.867
[officer]
...to the side, so there is
a service elevator...

26:05.019 --> 26:06.403
Where do you guys keep
the sugar?

26:07.708 --> 26:10.243
Barrett was supposed
to refill that. One second.

26:11.739 --> 26:13.315
Here, you can use my stash.

26:13.545 --> 26:14.505
Thanks.

26:16.349 --> 26:17.576
-You guys want donuts?
-No.

26:18.345 --> 26:19.496
I'll leave them out.

26:20.265 --> 26:23.529
[indistinct chatter]

26:24.029 --> 26:24.874
Sorry. Sorry.

26:25.027 --> 26:27.485
Sorry, guys. Sorry. Sorry, guys.

26:27.677 --> 26:29.597
[indistinct radio chatter]

26:45.532 --> 26:48.566
[woman] Cooper! Cooper.

26:48.721 --> 26:50.332
Hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey...

26:50.525 --> 26:53.289
I'm really glad I saw you again.
I can tell that you're upset.

26:53.521 --> 26:55.326
I am upset.
My daughter was hurt.

26:55.479 --> 26:56.976
-We can talk about it later.
-No, no, no.

26:57.206 --> 26:58.704
These girls just need
to be able to work things out
for themselves.

26:58.934 --> 27:00.854
-You know what I'm saying?
-To an extent, I do.

27:01.086 --> 27:02.966
But it's delicate.
Let's discuss it later.

27:03.121 --> 27:04.273
No. Hey!

27:05.924 --> 27:07.115
Don't mess with me, Cooper.

27:08.036 --> 27:09.456
I'm not someone to be provoked.

27:09.687 --> 27:12.413
I have a dark side.
You don't want to see it.

27:12.567 --> 27:15.216
Look... This is their day.

27:15.447 --> 27:17.136
Riley's been looking forward
to this for six months.

27:17.328 --> 27:18.750
-Let's just have fun, okay?
-Okay.

27:18.941 --> 27:20.900
Don't patronize me, Cooper.

27:21.092 --> 27:22.245
[man] Get him!

27:23.050 --> 27:24.932
[indistinct shouting]

27:25.815 --> 27:27.697
[crowd screaming]

27:29.195 --> 27:31.767
[officer] Don't move!
Hands behind your head!

27:33.418 --> 27:35.839
[clamoring continues]

27:52.236 --> 27:53.848
Get him out of here, quickly.

27:54.002 --> 27:55.499
[suspect grunts]

28:04.870 --> 28:07.019
What was that? A scalper?

28:07.211 --> 28:08.479
[Cooper] How about this?

28:08.671 --> 28:10.053
Why don't we get
the girls to get
a slice of pizza together?

28:10.476 --> 28:12.435
One p.m., Saturday at Carmine's?

28:12.588 --> 28:13.663
[stammers] Wait, what?

28:13.893 --> 28:15.659
Just so they have
a positive experience.

28:15.851 --> 28:17.043
We don't need them
to be best friends.

28:17.196 --> 28:19.846
They just need to coexist.
Not see each other as threats.

28:20.077 --> 28:22.035
-Sound like a plan?
-I'll ask Jody.

28:22.226 --> 28:23.840
Thank you.
I'm gonna get back to Riley.

28:24.032 --> 28:25.298
Enjoy the rest of the concert.

28:25.490 --> 28:26.412
You too.

28:27.410 --> 28:28.717
[chuckles]

28:28.870 --> 28:32.595
[Lady Raven performing
"Empathize"]

28:35.207 --> 28:36.243
[woman over radio]
<i> ...taken into custody.</i>

28:36.397 --> 28:38.969
<i> He was not our unsub.</i>

28:39.123 --> 28:42.655
<i> Repeating,</i>
<i> this is Dr. Josephine Grant.</i>

28:42.809 --> 28:46.419
<i> The man apprehended</i>
<i> in Concourse B</i>
<i> on west side of stadium</i>

28:46.649 --> 28:48.762
<i> is not our unsub.</i>

28:48.954 --> 28:51.334
<i> He's wanted</i>
<i> for a history of B and E's.</i>

28:51.489 --> 28:54.329
<i>He thought all this was for him</i>
<i> and he panicked.</i>

28:54.522 --> 28:56.941
<i> Our person won't panic.</i>

28:57.133 --> 29:00.857
<i> He's here and he's trying</i>
<i> to figure out a way out.</i>

29:02.164 --> 29:04.238
<i> I'm gonna give you back</i>
<i> to the unit commander.</i>

29:05.466 --> 29:07.156
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Empathize"]

29:07.347 --> 29:08.499
[commander over radio]
<i> Okay, I'm being told</i>

29:08.730 --> 29:12.110
<i> we have a potential match</i>
<i> in section 417, seat 12.</i>

29:12.301 --> 29:13.415
[radio beeps]

29:14.683 --> 29:16.564
<i> Reminding everyone,</i>
<i> visual markers.</i>

29:16.718 --> 29:19.560
<i> Surveillance footage</i>
<i> from area where</i>
<i> victims' bodies were found,</i>

29:19.790 --> 29:21.595
<i>recorded men of various builds.</i>

29:23.361 --> 29:26.434
<i> A redheaded male,</i>
<i> two African-American males</i>
<i> above average height.</i>

29:26.663 --> 29:28.852
<i> A male with white hair</i>
<i> in his 60s.</i>

29:29.045 --> 29:33.422
<i> A white male in his 30s</i>
<i> with a tattoo of a rabbit</i>
<i> or animal on his right arm.</i>

29:34.728 --> 29:37.108
<i> A white male with a scar</i>
<i> on his lower jaw.</i>

29:37.338 --> 29:41.217
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Empathize"]

29:46.402 --> 29:48.476
[crowd cheering]

29:48.667 --> 29:51.854
[commander over radio]<i> Uh,</i>
<i> there's a male near the ramp</i>
<i> on the south side of stadium</i>

29:52.047 --> 29:55.196
<i> wearing a yellow sweatshirt.</i>
<i> Engage with caution.</i>

29:56.809 --> 29:59.842
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Empathize"]

30:06.678 --> 30:09.635
Oh, shoot.
I forgot my credit card
at the T-shirt stand.

30:09.826 --> 30:10.518
I'll be right back.

30:11.016 --> 30:12.284
Dad, you keep leaving.

30:13.321 --> 30:15.472
I know.
After this, I won't leave you.

30:16.278 --> 30:17.698
You want me to come? I feel bad.

30:17.891 --> 30:19.043
No, you enjoy.

30:19.273 --> 30:20.501
Tell me everything I miss.

30:21.384 --> 30:22.921
Just in case we get separated,

30:23.152 --> 30:26.570
meet me at
the orange drink stand
right outside the tunnel.

30:26.800 --> 30:27.645
Just in case.

30:30.293 --> 30:33.097
[commander over radio]<i> FBI tents</i>
<i> are set up on the perimeter.</i>

30:33.290 --> 30:36.668
<i> Barricades are set up along</i>
<i>Market Street and Ninth Street.</i>

30:36.898 --> 30:39.165
<i> Ground personnel are stationed</i>
<i> at every exit.</i>

30:39.855 --> 30:41.737
<i>Open communication is essential.</i>

30:42.774 --> 30:45.079
<i> Continue check-ins</i>
<i> at five minute intervals.</i>

30:48.957 --> 30:50.454
[over radio]<i> Dr. Grant here.</i>

30:50.685 --> 30:53.219
<i> All sections be ready</i>
<i> for contingency four.</i>

30:54.294 --> 30:56.445 line:20%
<i> I've told you</i>
<i> how this is going to work.</i>

30:56.637 --> 30:58.825 line:20%
<i>He's realized he can't get out.</i>

30:58.979 --> 31:00.822 line:20%
<i> He's going to try</i>
<i> to cause a panic.</i>

31:02.321 --> 31:05.278 line:20%
<i> He's going to use the chaos</i>
<i> of 20,000 people to get by us.</i>

31:06.967 --> 31:10.039 line:20%
<i> He's going to make</i>
<i> a bomb call to police</i>
<i> or set off a fire alarm.</i>

31:10.499 --> 31:11.960 line:20%
<i> When that happens,</i>

31:12.151 --> 31:15.184
<i> only women and children</i>
<i> are let through.</i>

31:27.397 --> 31:30.429
[indistinct chatter]

31:42.412 --> 31:45.751
[indistinct chatter]

31:52.127 --> 31:53.777
[oil bubbling]

31:55.736 --> 31:59.078
[indistinct chatter continues]

32:19.468 --> 32:22.463
[oil bubbling vigorously]

32:27.148 --> 32:28.608
[woman gasps]

32:30.258 --> 32:31.526
[glass explodes]

32:31.718 --> 32:35.213
-[crowd screaming]
-[urgent radio chatter]

32:35.405 --> 32:36.480
[officer] Move! Move!

32:37.133 --> 32:41.011
[screaming continues]

32:45.273 --> 32:47.117
[screaming continues]

33:00.749 --> 33:02.899
[indistinct radio chatter]

33:04.321 --> 33:05.741
The hell are you doing out here?

33:07.163 --> 33:10.081
[voice wavering] Oh, sorry.
I just needed some air.

33:10.310 --> 33:11.809
There was
an accident in the kitchen.

33:12.001 --> 33:12.884
Uh... [sighs]

33:13.038 --> 33:16.032
I freaked out.
A friend got burned.

33:17.454 --> 33:18.529
[indistinct radio chatter]

33:18.721 --> 33:19.604
[radio beeps]

33:19.758 --> 33:21.256
Some sort of kitchen accident.
Great.

33:21.409 --> 33:24.941
It was very upsetting.
I think she's gonna be scarred.

33:25.134 --> 33:26.171
What's the code?

33:27.477 --> 33:28.168
Hamilton.

33:29.397 --> 33:30.433
Well, I'll get back.

33:31.125 --> 33:32.046
Let's see your card.

33:33.813 --> 33:35.386
The one you were given
at the presentation.

33:36.231 --> 33:37.039
Oh, yeah.

33:49.212 --> 33:50.517
[indistinct radio chatter]

33:54.740 --> 33:56.392
Don't tell my boss
I took a break, okay?

33:58.735 --> 34:02.382
By the way,
who was the older woman
who gave the presentation?

34:02.537 --> 34:04.534
She looked like
she was running the show.

34:05.070 --> 34:06.222
She's a profiler.

34:06.415 --> 34:08.335
She's taken down
ten of these guys.

34:08.527 --> 34:10.101
She's thought of everything.

34:11.138 --> 34:12.559
Well, that's a relief.

34:13.519 --> 34:16.092
[indistinct radio chatter]

34:19.088 --> 34:21.008
[indistinct chatter]

34:26.883 --> 34:30.723
[crying, hyperventilating]

34:34.178 --> 34:37.520
[cries echoing]

34:41.975 --> 34:44.048
[crying continues]

34:44.893 --> 34:45.853
[Riley] Dad.

34:46.505 --> 34:48.233
Dad, what are you doing?

34:49.693 --> 34:50.307
Got it.

34:50.960 --> 34:53.072
You're acting weird.
Is something wrong?

34:53.225 --> 34:54.262
-Do you wanna go home?
-No.

34:54.992 --> 34:56.835
Listen, I'll be honest with you.

34:57.027 --> 34:59.945
I just ran into
Jody's mom again,
and she started...

35:00.099 --> 35:00.867
You know how she is.

35:02.557 --> 35:05.015
I made friends
with the girls next to us.
Everything's already better.

35:05.667 --> 35:07.089
You're amazing.

35:07.281 --> 35:10.161
Let's just be together.
I want you to see
the rest of the concert.

35:10.929 --> 35:11.889
Deal.

35:13.771 --> 35:14.577
[Cooper imitates explosion]

35:14.808 --> 35:19.031
[crowd cheering]

35:19.952 --> 35:22.064
Hello, guys!

35:23.409 --> 35:25.636
How do y'all like my outfit?
Do you like it?

35:27.057 --> 35:28.516
[Riley, faint] Hope I get picked
for the "Dreamer Girl" song.

35:29.591 --> 35:30.322
Dad?

35:31.320 --> 35:32.356
Dad?

35:32.548 --> 35:33.854
[Lady Raven speaking
indistinctly]

35:34.008 --> 35:35.543
I'm sorry, Riley. What was that?

35:35.774 --> 35:37.963
I said I hope I get picked
for the "Dreamer Girl" song.

35:38.154 --> 35:41.880
They pick a girl out of
the audience and she gets to go
on stage with Lady Raven.

35:43.223 --> 35:45.298
Well, you never know.
We'll keep our fingers crossed.

35:45.490 --> 35:47.831
Yeah, she even gets
to go backstage and everything.

35:49.292 --> 35:50.827
Backstage, huh?

35:52.248 --> 35:53.707
Well, that is something.

35:53.860 --> 35:56.548
[funky guitar riff playing]

36:03.115 --> 36:05.881
[Lady Raven performing
"Love You"]

36:12.486 --> 36:14.751
[crowd singing along]

36:33.645 --> 36:36.563
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Love You"]

36:39.443 --> 36:40.786
-Hey.
-Hey.

36:40.979 --> 36:42.016
I assume you work for her.

36:43.168 --> 36:44.896
Every teenager in here
is devoted to her.

36:45.088 --> 36:46.623
She could start a cult.

36:46.855 --> 36:48.736
And they're hanging
on her every word.

36:49.465 --> 36:51.078
Must be something
to be that loved, right?

36:52.345 --> 36:54.650
I'm actually her uncle,
her mother's brother.

36:54.804 --> 36:56.455
And she's really great.

36:56.647 --> 36:57.722
Wow.

36:57.913 --> 36:58.988
Okay, listen.

37:00.793 --> 37:03.252
We're so excited to be here.
I'm Cooper.

37:03.482 --> 37:04.366
How you doing, man?

37:04.595 --> 37:06.170
That's my daughter, Riley.
Over there.

37:06.324 --> 37:07.475
The one losing her mind

37:07.667 --> 37:08.320
even more than the other girls
losing their minds.

37:08.512 --> 37:10.432
[Riley cheering]

37:12.429 --> 37:14.580
She just recovered
from having leukemia.

37:15.540 --> 37:16.884
Oh, no, it's okay now.
It's just...

37:17.729 --> 37:19.342
tough road for that little one.

37:20.379 --> 37:21.454
She doesn't want
anybody to know about it.

37:21.646 --> 37:22.989
She felt cursed.

37:23.143 --> 37:25.563
Like, she was chosen
to be cursed.

37:28.942 --> 37:30.785
But she's getting
over that feeling, so...

37:31.591 --> 37:32.743
Hey, I'm sorry
to dump that on you, it's just--

37:32.898 --> 37:34.088
-No, no.
-Look...

37:34.279 --> 37:37.774
I'm really happy we're here,
and I know we're nobodies,

37:37.966 --> 37:40.655
but please,
thank Lady Raven for us.

37:41.076 --> 37:42.881
Hey, what seats you guys in?

37:43.111 --> 37:46.030
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Love You"]

37:50.753 --> 37:53.787
[crowd singing along]

38:12.374 --> 38:13.372
[spotter] Excuse me.

38:14.792 --> 38:16.444
Sorry to bother you.
Could I talk to her
for a second?

38:16.635 --> 38:17.942
Of course.

38:19.439 --> 38:21.474
Thank you for coming
to the concert.
What's your name?

38:22.051 --> 38:22.395
Riley.

38:23.624 --> 38:25.352
Hey, Riley. We were wondering
if you would like to be

38:25.584 --> 38:27.965
Lady Raven's Dreamer Girl
at today's show.

38:28.579 --> 38:29.654
Oh, my God.

38:29.885 --> 38:32.149
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

38:32.342 --> 38:33.071
[Riley giggling]

38:33.225 --> 38:34.493
Is that a yes or a no?

38:34.991 --> 38:36.757
Yes! Yes. Dad!

38:37.948 --> 38:40.790
[Lady Raven performing
"Dead End"]

38:46.167 --> 38:49.199
-[song continues]
-[crowd cheering]

39:09.860 --> 39:10.820
Here, put these on.

39:13.315 --> 39:14.198
They're with us.

39:14.390 --> 39:15.505
We should talk with him.

39:15.697 --> 39:17.232
It's all good. He's with us.

39:18.539 --> 39:21.342
[whispering, indistinct]

39:34.282 --> 39:35.166
[spotter] You're all good.

39:35.357 --> 39:36.664
[Cooper] Yeah!

39:39.351 --> 39:40.619
Hey.

39:42.578 --> 39:44.383
Whoo-whoo-hoo!

39:44.613 --> 39:45.650
Yeah, baby!

39:45.879 --> 39:48.721
[Lady Raven continues singing]

40:13.529 --> 40:14.451
Thank you.

40:15.640 --> 40:17.445
Hey, sweetie. Are you excited?

40:18.443 --> 40:20.594
Um, so, I'm sure you know
how this works, right?

40:20.787 --> 40:23.052
When Lady Raven tells the crowd
she's doing "Dreamer Girl,"

40:23.282 --> 40:25.011
she's gonna ask
for you to come out.

40:25.240 --> 40:27.814
Okay, you're gonna walk
to that spot
on stage right there.

40:27.968 --> 40:29.811
You guys are gonna dance
back and forth.

40:30.040 --> 40:31.693
You just have
to follow her lead, okay?

40:31.884 --> 40:34.073
It's not about being good,
it's about goofing around.

40:34.611 --> 40:35.418
Okay?

40:36.186 --> 40:37.107
You good?

40:37.874 --> 40:38.911
You good, Riley?

40:39.142 --> 40:40.179
I'm scared.

40:40.371 --> 40:41.599
Hmm, you know what?

40:41.830 --> 40:44.441
When she takes your hand,
you're not gonna be, I promise.

40:44.594 --> 40:45.631
[song ends]

40:45.824 --> 40:48.319
It's gonna be so good.
Okay, I'll be back.

40:51.123 --> 40:52.966
Mmm. You're good.

40:53.158 --> 40:56.038
[crowd cheering]

41:01.798 --> 41:04.986
[cheering continues]

41:09.134 --> 41:11.398
[cheering intensifies]

41:13.280 --> 41:15.392
[Lady Raven] This is my favorite
part of the concert.

41:18.887 --> 41:21.882
Looks like our Dreamer Girl
is a Riley?

41:22.689 --> 41:25.416
[crowd cheers intensify]

41:25.607 --> 41:27.336
[Lady Raven] Where's Riley?

41:28.373 --> 41:30.254
Riley, you wanna
come dance with me?

41:30.445 --> 41:32.251
[crowd cheering]

41:36.782 --> 41:39.124
["Dreamer Girl"
by Lady Raven begins]

41:52.833 --> 41:55.176
[Lady Raven performing
"Dreamer Girl"]

42:06.697 --> 42:08.310
Don't tell me to breathe!

42:08.502 --> 42:11.382
[song continues]

42:28.739 --> 42:30.621
[both shrieking]

42:30.851 --> 42:32.156
You little beast!

42:34.037 --> 42:36.917
[Lady Raven continues
performing "Dreamer Girl"]

42:42.986 --> 42:44.867
[music fades]

42:57.001 --> 42:59.191
[crowd cheering]

43:01.149 --> 43:02.532
[tour manager chuckles]

43:02.723 --> 43:04.758
Your daughter's
never gonna forget today.

43:04.912 --> 43:07.831
["Dreamer Girl" continues]

43:31.408 --> 43:33.444
[crowd cheering]

43:38.859 --> 43:40.933
[song ends]

43:41.124 --> 43:43.850
[Dr. Grant] If anyone tries
to get backstage, let me know.

43:45.464 --> 43:47.153
[crowd cheering]

43:47.346 --> 43:48.727
[Cooper] Whoo!

43:52.836 --> 43:55.256
-What? What?
-[Riley laughing]

43:58.443 --> 44:00.633
I'm just gonna check and see
if there's space.

44:06.738 --> 44:08.888
She was about to collapse.
Where should I put her?

44:10.463 --> 44:11.730
Right through there.

44:19.027 --> 44:20.447
You're gonna be okay.

44:20.639 --> 44:21.599
Don't try and stand up.

44:21.792 --> 44:23.136
[girl cries]

44:23.288 --> 44:25.170
I could have been
a Dreamer Girl!

44:25.362 --> 44:27.244
[indistinct chatter]

44:30.008 --> 44:31.737
Hey, we're gonna
get you some juice.

44:31.967 --> 44:33.542
You haven't eaten
anything all day, I bet.

44:34.502 --> 44:35.539
You're safe now.

44:35.769 --> 44:37.804
You're gonna be fine
in about 30 minutes, okay?

44:38.034 --> 44:39.418
Hey, there you are.

44:39.609 --> 44:41.567
He's a gem. Can we keep him?

44:41.721 --> 44:43.066
He's really good with them.

44:43.296 --> 44:45.063
Oh! You helped this girl?

44:45.216 --> 44:46.559
Anyone would have done the same.

44:46.752 --> 44:48.135
Wow. Thank you.

44:48.287 --> 44:50.592
[crowd cheering]

44:50.823 --> 44:51.898
Okay. Come on up.

44:53.203 --> 44:55.084
Okay, so you guys can watch
from the side here.

44:55.276 --> 44:56.159
This is gonna be her last song.

44:56.352 --> 44:58.349
It's the encore,
so you just enjoy, okay?

44:58.503 --> 44:59.425
-Okay, thank you.
-Okay!

44:59.655 --> 45:00.729
Bye!

45:02.189 --> 45:04.492
[crowd roaring]

45:15.245 --> 45:20.122
[crowd chanting] Lady Raven!
Lady Raven! Lady Raven!

45:32.104 --> 45:33.332
[inhaling deeply]

45:38.324 --> 45:39.707
[man] I don't understand.
I don't understand it.

45:39.899 --> 45:41.012
I said Lactaid milk.

45:41.242 --> 45:43.047
Lactaid milk, not whole milk.

45:43.239 --> 45:45.429
You won't stop until I doo-doo
on myself, now, will you?

45:45.583 --> 45:46.389
Will you?

45:47.618 --> 45:49.307
Everyone needs a break
when they're starting out.

45:49.499 --> 45:50.421
[loud cheering]

45:50.651 --> 45:54.376
And I got mine
from the dopest person ever.

45:54.529 --> 45:56.988
I owe a lot to The Thinker.

45:57.218 --> 46:00.443
[melodic guitar riff playing]

46:05.666 --> 46:08.546
[Lady Raven performing "Divine"]

46:25.635 --> 46:28.553
[The Thinker joins in]

46:57.929 --> 46:59.004
Hey, when this is over,

46:59.158 --> 47:01.040
can we go out the back here
to get to our car?

47:01.271 --> 47:02.998
Oh, yeah.
That's fine. No worries.

47:03.153 --> 47:04.343
-Thanks.
-Sure.

47:04.534 --> 47:07.414
[Lady Raven continues performing
"Divine"]

47:20.931 --> 47:23.773
[indistinct chatter, laughter]

47:25.923 --> 47:27.651
I'll see you tonight, yeah?
All right.

47:32.375 --> 47:33.527
How you doin'?

47:34.679 --> 47:37.559
[laughter and chatter]

47:38.365 --> 47:40.209
[Cooper laughs]

47:42.590 --> 47:44.434
[indistinct radio chatter]

47:45.239 --> 47:46.277
Oh, my God.

47:46.469 --> 47:48.042
[fans exclaiming]

47:49.079 --> 47:50.999
[indistinct radio chatter]

47:54.111 --> 47:55.415
Dad, look, look!

47:57.106 --> 47:59.256
[woman] Mr. The Thinker,
I got that kombucha
just like you asked.

47:59.448 --> 48:00.869
No, that's feral fig.

48:01.061 --> 48:03.596
I specifically said I wanted
honeysuckle sour kombucha,
bitch.

48:03.826 --> 48:05.976
[stammering] Of course you did.
I can fix that.

48:06.206 --> 48:07.857
-Knock on the door.
-Yes.

48:08.049 --> 48:09.777
Knock harder. Damn!

48:10.891 --> 48:12.428
-Hey!
-Hi!

48:13.503 --> 48:15.039
-You killed it.
-Thank you. Great show.

48:15.231 --> 48:17.496
Thank you. You too, you too.
Going back to LA?

48:17.726 --> 48:18.533
Yeah. See you there.

48:18.686 --> 48:21.298
-Yeah. DM me. Bye.
-All right. Bye.

48:21.490 --> 48:23.256
[indistinct chatter]

48:25.100 --> 48:26.367
[Riley gasps]

48:35.392 --> 48:36.621
[The Thinker] Hot zaddy!

48:36.773 --> 48:40.000
[laughs] Oww!

48:40.192 --> 48:41.804
[Dr. Grant over radio]
<i> All male stadium employees</i>

48:42.035 --> 48:44.032
<i> should be run</i>
<i> through the system again.</i>

48:44.262 --> 48:47.334
<i> We will stop every male</i>
<i> in attendance at this concert.</i>

48:48.103 --> 48:49.715
One of you is going
to be talking to the Butcher

48:49.869 --> 48:52.019
in the next 20 minutes.

48:52.211 --> 48:54.131
You may count on it.

48:54.361 --> 48:55.514
[radio beeps]

48:56.281 --> 48:58.777
[excited chatter, cheers]

48:59.007 --> 49:01.004
Hey. All right,
she wants to say bye

49:01.197 --> 49:02.732
and thank you to you guys.
She's just got to get done

49:02.924 --> 49:04.077
some radio
meet and greets, okay?

49:04.308 --> 49:05.345
-All right.
-This is some concert gear

49:05.574 --> 49:06.688
-for you guys.
-Thank you.

49:06.841 --> 49:08.071
[chuckles] You're welcome.

49:08.301 --> 49:09.606
And thank you again
for all of your help.

49:09.838 --> 49:11.066
Of course.

49:11.257 --> 49:12.948
All right, so you guys are
gonna go out the back way.

49:14.368 --> 49:15.828
Uh...

49:16.019 --> 49:17.441
Yeah. Okay,
so you're gonna go through
a police inspection there.

49:17.633 --> 49:19.130
They'll ask you some questions.
It's nothing.

49:19.322 --> 49:20.705
We just have
some extra security tonight.

49:21.933 --> 49:23.085
It's a pain in the butt,
but we've all gotta do it.

49:23.239 --> 49:25.658
Only Lady Raven and her
very close group are excluded.

49:25.850 --> 49:27.195
And you were
so great tonight, angel.

49:27.387 --> 49:28.385
She'll be out soon, okay?

49:28.576 --> 49:29.921
-Okay.
-Okay!

49:32.955 --> 49:35.527
[Riley] Oh, my gosh, Dad,
there's so much stuff in here.

49:35.720 --> 49:36.757
Look!

49:37.985 --> 49:40.173
Oh, my gosh, Dad,
there's so much in here.

49:40.327 --> 49:41.902
Dad, there's tattoos.

49:42.938 --> 49:45.012
Dad, there's
three drink bottles.

49:45.204 --> 49:46.703
Oh, there's two white ones.
We'd be matching.

49:46.855 --> 49:48.469
Do you want one?
We could be matching, Dad.

49:48.623 --> 49:49.697
Yeah. Great.

49:50.351 --> 49:51.886
[Riley] Oh, this is so cool.

49:54.152 --> 49:55.649
There's no sign of him at all?

49:55.803 --> 49:57.454
He's playing his hand very well.

49:57.646 --> 49:59.720
But this is an inevitability.

49:59.951 --> 50:03.561
There were 20,642
in attendance today.

50:03.791 --> 50:06.132
There were 3,000 men here.

50:06.324 --> 50:08.629
We will have photos and data
on all of them.

50:08.821 --> 50:11.356
We're questioning everyone
as they leave.

50:11.548 --> 50:13.621
He is one of those 3,000.

50:14.313 --> 50:15.579
We will catch him.

50:18.613 --> 50:20.035
He's out of moves.

50:20.265 --> 50:21.839
I'll give you an update soon.

50:23.107 --> 50:25.027
[tense music playing]

50:33.167 --> 50:34.204
Riley!

50:35.433 --> 50:37.161
-Did you have fun up there?
-Yes.

50:37.967 --> 50:39.043
That's so amazing.

50:39.657 --> 50:40.847
[Riley laughs nervously]

50:41.040 --> 50:43.381
Thank you. My dad got it for me.
It's an antique.

50:45.840 --> 50:48.144
Hey. I think you heard
about my daughter's condition?

50:48.297 --> 50:49.603
Can I talk to you alone
for a moment?

50:49.795 --> 50:51.100
Just for like one minute?

50:51.792 --> 50:53.135
Of course.

50:53.289 --> 50:54.557
I'm gonna talk
to your dad for a second.

50:54.711 --> 50:55.517
BRB.

50:55.977 --> 50:57.476
We'll leave soon, honey.

50:58.857 --> 50:59.971
[Lady Raven] Wait outside.
Just give me a second.

51:00.164 --> 51:01.431
I'll leave right after.

51:05.539 --> 51:07.728
[Cooper laughs]

51:08.919 --> 51:10.416
Thank you for everything
you've done for Riley.

51:10.608 --> 51:11.684
She's an angel.

51:11.876 --> 51:13.411
I feel so close to her.
I don't know why.

51:13.565 --> 51:14.833
She really is special.

51:14.986 --> 51:16.561
[Cooper inhales deeply]

51:16.753 --> 51:19.671
I don't know if you know
anything about carbon monoxide.

51:21.130 --> 51:24.548
Your body wants the poison.
It wants it more than oxygen.

51:24.739 --> 51:27.811
That's why it can be
so very lethal in small spaces.

51:27.965 --> 51:29.731
You need to know about these
sort of things as a firefighter.

51:29.885 --> 51:31.883
-[laughs]
-I'm sorry?

51:33.533 --> 51:36.221
Well... the reason I wanted
to talk to you...

51:38.295 --> 51:39.293
is...

51:40.869 --> 51:42.405
...I think you're
looking for me.

51:45.515 --> 51:47.050
I mean, all of you.

51:49.394 --> 51:50.200
Hold on.

51:51.850 --> 51:53.963
Oh, wait, I gotta press mute
so he doesn't hear us.

51:56.191 --> 52:00.222
[shaky breaths, groaning]

52:01.412 --> 52:02.872
<i> Help!</i>

52:03.026 --> 52:04.446
[Cooper] Yep.

52:06.942 --> 52:08.171
You see that little box?

52:09.362 --> 52:10.322
That is going to release
carbon monoxide...

52:10.514 --> 52:11.398
<i> Help me!</i>

52:11.590 --> 52:12.779
...and kill him
within five minutes.

52:12.933 --> 52:14.776
He is going to die
if I am caught.

52:15.006 --> 52:16.696
That's just an absolute fact.

52:17.848 --> 52:19.116
I can do it from here,
from this device,

52:19.347 --> 52:21.151
like... [chuckles]
...calling an Uber.

52:22.379 --> 52:24.031
You caught me. I admit it.

52:24.761 --> 52:27.103
But... you can save him.

52:28.908 --> 52:31.443
I'll let him go
if you do one thing.

52:32.710 --> 52:34.168
What you're going to do
in front of everybody

52:34.361 --> 52:35.552
is you're going to ask
me and my daughter

52:35.743 --> 52:37.624
if we want a ride
in your limousine.

52:38.776 --> 52:40.275
And then you're gonna
drive us out of here.

52:41.503 --> 52:44.115
I will press it right now
if you signal them.

52:46.842 --> 52:49.490
Save him. Catch me.

52:50.643 --> 52:52.679
Save him. Catch me.

52:53.562 --> 52:54.905
By the way, it was a great show.

52:57.094 --> 52:58.631
His name is Spencer.

52:58.822 --> 53:00.205
He's 22 years old.

53:01.165 --> 53:02.432
He's into
sustainable agriculture.

53:02.662 --> 53:04.928
[Spencer]
<i> Somebody help me, please!</i>

53:06.042 --> 53:07.808
<i> Please help me!</i>

53:08.845 --> 53:10.036
<i> Help!</i>

53:10.842 --> 53:13.414
[indistinct radio chatter]

53:23.936 --> 53:25.473
[Cooper laughs]

53:25.664 --> 53:26.816
Whoa.

53:30.043 --> 53:31.848
Right through here.
Right this way.

53:32.040 --> 53:33.000
Move along.

53:33.230 --> 53:34.343
-Through here.
-All right.

53:35.112 --> 53:37.032
[Riley gasps excitedly]

53:39.412 --> 53:40.757
These three are cleared.

53:43.981 --> 53:46.746
[indistinct chatter]

53:58.612 --> 53:59.765
[limousine engine starts]

54:01.877 --> 54:03.105
[officer] To your left.

54:03.297 --> 54:04.449
Everybody forward.

54:05.294 --> 54:06.793
Through.
Right through here, sir.

54:08.136 --> 54:09.596
Through here. Exit through here.

54:09.749 --> 54:11.822
-Get out, let's go.
-[officer 2] Let's just
move along.

54:28.681 --> 54:29.986
Limo's clear.

54:51.645 --> 54:53.142
You can just drop us off
on the near corner.

54:53.334 --> 54:54.448
We're parked nearby.

55:08.964 --> 55:10.345
[Riley sighs happily]

55:11.229 --> 55:13.341
-Um, can I...?
-Yeah.

55:18.679 --> 55:20.022
-Hey, Riley.
-Mm-hm?

55:20.791 --> 55:21.904
Can I visit your home?

55:22.787 --> 55:24.171
-What?
-Yeah.

55:24.363 --> 55:25.476
How about right now?

55:26.244 --> 55:27.127
I could drop you there.

55:28.395 --> 55:30.276
Oh, my God. Oh, my God,
this isn't happening.

55:30.467 --> 55:31.466
Is this happening?

55:31.619 --> 55:33.963
Oh, my God, that would be,
like, so incredible.

55:34.155 --> 55:35.038
Oh, my God!

55:35.229 --> 55:36.612
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

55:36.805 --> 55:38.648
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

55:39.492 --> 55:41.643
Mom. Mom, you won't believe it.
You will not believe it.

55:41.835 --> 55:44.523
Me and Dad are in a limousine,
and we're here with Lady Raven.

55:45.522 --> 55:47.095
No, I'm not making it up.
I'm not making it up.

55:47.288 --> 55:49.092
I got picked
to be the Dreamer Girl onstage,

55:49.246 --> 55:52.127
and then she asked
to drop us off and now she wants
to see our house.

55:53.470 --> 55:55.199
Yeah, I know, I know.
Dad can't believe it either.

55:55.390 --> 55:56.850
He's just sitting there.

55:57.042 --> 55:58.732
Can she come? Mom, come on.

55:58.924 --> 56:00.190
She doesn't care
about the carpet.

56:00.690 --> 56:02.802
Mom, please. Please? Say yes.

56:04.876 --> 56:06.065
Mom said yes. Mom said yes!
[laughs]

56:06.257 --> 56:07.102
-Great.
-Thank you.

56:07.332 --> 56:08.100
Huh.

56:09.407 --> 56:11.673
Jeremiah. We're gonna be
visiting a friend's house.

56:11.825 --> 56:12.556
[beeps]

56:12.747 --> 56:13.516
What's the address, sweetheart?

56:13.745 --> 56:15.398
108 Monk Road.

56:15.896 --> 56:17.010
Mm-hm.

56:46.386 --> 56:47.653
[Riley giggles]

56:47.846 --> 56:51.455
[all laughing excitedly]

56:51.687 --> 56:53.607
-Oh...
-[laughter]

56:54.605 --> 56:55.910
-Dad's acting strange.
-How?

56:56.140 --> 56:57.293
Oh, I'll tell you later.

57:01.325 --> 57:02.170
Just wait here.

57:03.092 --> 57:04.436
[door shuts]

57:08.314 --> 57:09.082
[Riley] Um...

57:10.234 --> 57:12.730
This is Lady Raven.
She's... my friend.

57:13.421 --> 57:15.456
-Pleasure to meet you.
-It's an honor to meet you.

57:15.687 --> 57:17.569
We feel like
we already know you. [laughs]

57:18.144 --> 57:18.912
My name is Rachel.

57:19.065 --> 57:20.334
Thank you for letting me visit.

57:20.526 --> 57:22.638
I just got to know
your daughter.
I think she's wonderful.

57:23.174 --> 57:24.481
She is.

57:24.635 --> 57:25.632
And this is Logan.

57:25.862 --> 57:26.707
Hi, Logan.

57:26.861 --> 57:28.052
I saw you on TV.

57:28.244 --> 57:29.972
-You did?
-Wow.

57:30.203 --> 57:31.201
Well, let's not stay out here.

57:31.392 --> 57:32.929
Come in, if you can.
Have a bite.

57:34.043 --> 57:35.963
-That sounds great.
-Come.

57:41.569 --> 57:42.875
[Rachel] Lady R-Raven?

57:43.066 --> 57:45.101
Um... [laughs]
I just made a couple things.

57:45.255 --> 57:46.600
Nothing fancy
like you're used to.

57:46.829 --> 57:49.595
I would have made more
if I had more things.

57:49.748 --> 57:51.285
I love everything. I can't wait.

57:52.130 --> 57:53.857
-Can I show you my room?
-Of course.

57:54.088 --> 57:55.470
Logan, help me clean!

58:11.484 --> 58:13.633
I'll kill young Spencer if you
say anything in front of them.

58:15.094 --> 58:17.206
If you send a text
or if the police show up,
I'll kill him.

58:18.433 --> 58:20.239
I think you know
I'm not bluffing.

58:21.276 --> 58:22.581
I'm in control.

58:24.424 --> 58:26.575
I don't know
what you think you're doing.

58:27.419 --> 58:29.263
[Lady Raven]
I won't do anything.

58:29.416 --> 58:31.106
[Cooper] Okay.

58:34.332 --> 58:36.021
[Rachel] I made the pie
to celebrate Riley.

58:36.214 --> 58:37.597
She got a wonderful report card.

58:38.671 --> 58:40.668
Is it fluffy?
It's a Martha Stewart recipe.

58:41.168 --> 58:43.088
Perfect. Just the right amount.

58:44.009 --> 58:44.777
I love your necklace.

58:46.083 --> 58:49.770
Cooper got it for me on sale.
He's good at finding bargains.

58:49.923 --> 58:51.190
Always comes home
with something special.

58:51.343 --> 58:52.496
[laughs]

58:52.650 --> 58:54.455
What's it like to do a concert?

58:54.685 --> 58:57.794
I'm a theater teacher
for the fifth graders.

58:57.986 --> 58:59.830
It must be so much work,
I can't even imagine.

58:59.983 --> 59:00.867
[laughs]

59:01.097 --> 59:02.787
It was actually
very strange today.

59:03.017 --> 59:04.783
Not like a normal concert day.

59:05.245 --> 59:06.857
Oh, really? Why is that?

59:10.237 --> 59:11.697
[sets down plate]

59:11.889 --> 59:14.001
Do you know
who the Butcher is, Rachel?

59:14.884 --> 59:16.073
The Butcher?

59:16.881 --> 59:18.570
Um... [stammers]

59:18.762 --> 59:22.641
You mean, crazy person
who does that to people? I--

59:23.715 --> 59:25.981
Yes, I've heard of him. Uh...

59:27.172 --> 59:29.169
He's a monster.
That's all I can say.

59:29.399 --> 59:31.012
My friends
and I have had nightmares.

59:31.818 --> 59:33.278
Well, apparently,
he made a mistake.

59:34.544 --> 59:37.003
About two weeks ago,
the FBI and police came to me

59:37.232 --> 59:38.769
and they told me
they had found out

59:39.000 --> 59:41.303
