01:12:58.969 --> 01:12:59.852
Keep eyes on him.

01:13:00.005 --> 01:13:01.350
Move! Move! Move!

01:13:01.581 --> 01:13:02.886
-[door bangs]
-Go! Go!

01:13:04.346 --> 01:13:05.497
[man with southern accent]
Thank you for standing by, sir.

01:13:05.650 --> 01:13:07.149
I'mma drive her on out of here.

01:13:07.379 --> 01:13:08.492
[Jeremiah] Yes, sir.

01:13:11.295 --> 01:13:12.948
-[limo starts]
-Extracting civilian asset.

01:13:13.101 --> 01:13:15.097
-Support. Support.
-Eyes open. Watch corners.

01:13:15.289 --> 01:13:16.557
What's happening?

01:13:16.749 --> 01:13:18.169
[officer]<i> There's something</i>
<i> in the kitchen closet.</i>

01:13:18.400 --> 01:13:21.088
<i> A tunnel. It appears to lead</i>
<i> to the neighbor's yard.</i>

01:13:21.319 --> 01:13:23.239
[officer] Tell 'em to move out,
right now.

01:13:26.003 --> 01:13:27.808
[officer 2]
Perimeter SWAT member down.

01:13:28.883 --> 01:13:30.958
SWAT member
in neighbor's yard down.

01:13:39.675 --> 01:13:41.672
-[engine shuts off]
-[car door opens]

01:13:44.858 --> 01:13:46.816
[footsteps approaching]

01:13:50.733 --> 01:13:52.730
[cries out]

01:13:54.267 --> 01:13:55.074
[gasping]

01:13:58.529 --> 01:14:00.449
Sorry, we got interrupted.

01:14:05.519 --> 01:14:06.938
-[handcuffs rattling]
-[car door slams]

01:14:07.130 --> 01:14:08.321
[car door opens]

01:14:09.359 --> 01:14:11.009
-[groans]
-[engine starts]

01:14:11.240 --> 01:14:13.121
I have a safe place
about ten minutes from here.

01:14:13.851 --> 01:14:15.388
Luckily, it has a garage.

01:14:16.079 --> 01:14:18.114
A lot of places
have fire code violations

01:14:18.306 --> 01:14:21.148
and stay vacant for years.

01:14:22.337 --> 01:14:24.565
Wasted space, I always thought.

01:14:29.211 --> 01:14:31.093
[indistinct chatter]

01:14:32.974 --> 01:14:36.046
[Cooper] When I saw you waiting
behind the curtain on stage,

01:14:36.239 --> 01:14:37.774
I got the urge.

01:14:38.850 --> 01:14:40.041
It's strange
when I get the urge.

01:14:41.347 --> 01:14:44.841
I think it's when I see someone
who thinks they're whole.

01:14:45.033 --> 01:14:46.953
[car horns honking]

01:14:48.335 --> 01:14:49.795
That could never be true.

01:14:49.949 --> 01:14:51.869
Everyone's in pieces.

01:15:04.578 --> 01:15:06.077
[window clicks and whirs]

01:15:06.231 --> 01:15:07.842
Oh shit! It's Lady Raven.

01:15:07.997 --> 01:15:09.187
-[Lady Raven] Help me.
-[woman] Why?

01:15:09.840 --> 01:15:11.260
Wait, what's going on?

01:15:11.452 --> 01:15:12.989
Call the police.

01:15:13.143 --> 01:15:15.369
[people clamoring]

01:15:21.244 --> 01:15:23.242
-[woman] Is that actually
Lady Raven?
-[man] No way!

01:15:24.048 --> 01:15:25.853
[limousine horn honks]

01:15:26.083 --> 01:15:29.616
[handcuffs rattling]

01:15:30.385 --> 01:15:31.114
[grunting]

01:15:31.345 --> 01:15:32.650
[handcuffs continue rattling]

01:15:32.842 --> 01:15:36.528
[pedestrians chattering]

01:15:36.721 --> 01:15:38.871
[straining]

01:15:40.023 --> 01:15:41.328
[excited chatter]

01:15:42.096 --> 01:15:45.207
[handcuffs rattling]

01:15:53.233 --> 01:15:55.077
[excited chatter]

01:15:55.269 --> 01:15:57.572
[all shouting, screaming]

01:16:00.490 --> 01:16:01.643
Can you see her?

01:16:01.835 --> 01:16:05.290
[sirens blaring]

01:16:10.206 --> 01:16:13.356
[rapid footsteps approaching]

01:16:15.314 --> 01:16:19.039
[indistinct chatter]

01:16:23.109 --> 01:16:24.299
[officer] He's in the car.

01:16:25.374 --> 01:16:27.102
Move civilians away
from the vehicle.

01:16:28.331 --> 01:16:29.368
Move, move! Back, back, back.

01:16:29.561 --> 01:16:31.442
[chaotic chatter]

01:16:32.978 --> 01:16:35.781
[air hissing]

01:16:36.011 --> 01:16:37.625
[SWAT officer]
We assume you are armed.

01:16:37.816 --> 01:16:39.774
We will not come closer.

01:16:40.005 --> 01:16:41.964
Get out of the vehicle.

01:16:42.118 --> 01:16:44.000
I will not ask again.

01:16:51.065 --> 01:16:52.947
-[gunfire]
-[crowd screaming]

01:17:05.197 --> 01:17:07.615
[glass clinking]

01:17:10.457 --> 01:17:13.837
[indistinct shouting]

01:17:14.068 --> 01:17:16.140
It's only a SWAT helmet
and gear propped up.

01:17:16.602 --> 01:17:17.562
He must have been
with the crowd

01:17:17.754 --> 01:17:19.405
when we pulled them
away from the limo.

01:17:19.597 --> 01:17:22.246
Check all the stores.
Do not let the crowd leave.

01:17:24.051 --> 01:17:27.162
[sirens blare]

01:17:48.167 --> 01:17:50.280
[speech not audible]

01:18:12.629 --> 01:18:14.932
[indistinct radio chatter]

01:18:19.540 --> 01:18:22.191
They say you lecture on this.

01:18:23.266 --> 01:18:25.377
What would I hear
at one of your lectures?

01:18:28.334 --> 01:18:32.481
This individual is not
a projection of our fears.

01:18:32.635 --> 01:18:34.978
He is real,
comfortable and thriving.

01:18:35.938 --> 01:18:37.475
He doesn't set off
warning signals

01:18:37.628 --> 01:18:38.857
in our nervous system,

01:18:39.087 --> 01:18:40.891
but he is profoundly different.

01:18:42.044 --> 01:18:43.771 line:20%
A parent might have sensed this
at the beginning,

01:18:43.964 --> 01:18:46.115 line:20%
but no one else after could.

01:18:49.916 --> 01:18:52.374
Your children
are with your sister.

01:18:52.528 --> 01:18:54.639
It's not too late
to take up our offer.

01:18:55.599 --> 01:18:57.021
We can put you
all together somewhere.

01:18:57.212 --> 01:18:58.325
No. [clears throat]

01:18:58.556 --> 01:19:00.169
I don't want
to be around people.

01:19:02.128 --> 01:19:04.854
There are two cruisers
outside, all night.

01:19:05.085 --> 01:19:06.199
Thank you.

01:19:15.184 --> 01:19:17.028
[keyboard clattering]

01:19:35.382 --> 01:19:36.342
[igniter clicking]

01:19:54.660 --> 01:19:56.542
[sighs]

01:19:58.385 --> 01:20:00.843
-[Cooper] You always do that.
-[Rachel screams, gasps]

01:20:02.071 --> 01:20:03.914
You always stand
with your left hand on your hip

01:20:04.106 --> 01:20:05.643
like it's holding you up.

01:20:05.834 --> 01:20:07.717
[Rachel gasps]

01:20:07.871 --> 01:20:09.330
Cooper.

01:20:10.597 --> 01:20:12.631
It's funny how we knew
each other so well.

01:20:13.899 --> 01:20:16.204
I guess we know things
without knowing them.

01:20:16.395 --> 01:20:17.663
[stammers]

01:20:17.854 --> 01:20:20.044
I'm sure they've
made a mistake, Cooper.

01:20:20.197 --> 01:20:21.924
I'm sure
it's a misunderstanding.

01:20:22.577 --> 01:20:24.651
I'm not great
at a lot of things Rachel,

01:20:24.804 --> 01:20:27.454
but keeping
my two lives separate

01:20:27.684 --> 01:20:29.297
is not one of them.

01:20:29.451 --> 01:20:31.641
It's a big mix-up.
I'll tell them.

01:20:31.832 --> 01:20:32.754
[laughs nervously]

01:20:32.946 --> 01:20:35.057
When I had
a second to think about it,

01:20:36.478 --> 01:20:38.707
it kinda dawned on me
how this might have happened.

01:20:39.858 --> 01:20:42.700
Maybe the trap
wasn't set there at the concert.

01:20:43.698 --> 01:20:45.004
Maybe it was set here.

01:20:45.158 --> 01:20:46.310
I--

01:20:46.501 --> 01:20:47.845
I'm not following you.

01:20:48.498 --> 01:20:50.764
Well, maybe it kind of
dawned on you, too.

01:20:51.571 --> 01:20:55.027
The late nights, the jewelry.

01:20:56.178 --> 01:20:58.713
Maybe you thought
I was having an affair.

01:21:00.633 --> 01:21:01.938
[breathes shakily]

01:21:03.552 --> 01:21:04.512
I did.

01:21:05.855 --> 01:21:07.431
But that didn't feel right.

01:21:08.928 --> 01:21:11.731
What was it about it
that didn't feel right, Rachel?

01:21:12.845 --> 01:21:14.996
The smell of cleaning fluid
on your clothes.

01:21:16.455 --> 01:21:19.372
Not the type at the firehouse,
the type you smell at hospitals.

01:21:21.255 --> 01:21:23.136
[exhales]

01:21:24.442 --> 01:21:26.400
Nothing I could have done
about that, I'm afraid.

01:21:30.471 --> 01:21:32.391
I saw you make up a lie once.

01:21:33.619 --> 01:21:34.926
To our neighbor.

01:21:35.079 --> 01:21:37.229
About why we couldn't
come to his party.

01:21:37.459 --> 01:21:39.763
He sort of surprised us
at our car.

01:21:41.108 --> 01:21:44.065
You lied so convincingly...

01:21:45.139 --> 01:21:46.792
so honestly
off the top of your head

01:21:46.945 --> 01:21:48.059
right in front of me.

01:21:49.633 --> 01:21:51.936
No one would ever know
you were lying.

01:21:53.243 --> 01:21:54.394
It gave me chills.

01:21:55.009 --> 01:21:55.969
I thought...

01:21:57.120 --> 01:21:59.233
"Where did he learn to do that?"

01:22:03.226 --> 01:22:04.686
Can I take it from here?

01:22:04.877 --> 01:22:06.414
Just to see if I got this right.

01:22:07.220 --> 01:22:09.640
A small consolation prize.

01:22:11.983 --> 01:22:13.557
[metallic scrape and ring]

01:22:14.863 --> 01:22:19.010
You follow me one day...
to the safe house on Brewster.

01:22:20.200 --> 01:22:23.157
The one I go to
when I just want to think, plan,

01:22:23.349 --> 01:22:24.847
not to do anything.

01:22:26.075 --> 01:22:29.724
I find it just
as comforting as the doing.

01:22:31.758 --> 01:22:35.100
And then,
if I'm guessing correctly,

01:22:35.291 --> 01:22:37.211
you went back on your own.

01:22:39.208 --> 01:22:40.361
And I broke in.

01:22:41.398 --> 01:22:42.780
But there's nothing in there,
Rachel.

01:22:42.971 --> 01:22:45.660
Just a chair and a table.

01:22:46.851 --> 01:22:48.848
And then the thought
just came to me.

01:22:49.039 --> 01:22:50.691
[breathing shakily]
I couldn't get rid of it,

01:22:50.882 --> 01:22:52.380
the feeling just kept
coming back to me.

01:22:53.187 --> 01:22:54.799
I had a receipt from your wallet

01:22:55.030 --> 01:22:56.758
when I went through it
from before.

01:22:56.988 --> 01:23:02.442
A receipt from the concert,
and I left it there.

01:23:02.634 --> 01:23:04.515
And then I found a payphone
and called the police

01:23:04.668 --> 01:23:06.165
to say that it might...

01:23:06.895 --> 01:23:08.355
that it might be...

01:23:09.622 --> 01:23:11.119
...the Butcher.

01:23:12.348 --> 01:23:14.268
I tore it so it would look
like a mistake.

01:23:15.228 --> 01:23:16.304
Your mistake.

01:23:18.108 --> 01:23:19.722
I didn't know what would happen.

01:23:19.876 --> 01:23:22.141
I just thought it would
get them closer to you.

01:23:23.523 --> 01:23:26.442
And maybe I was wrong.
Maybe they would prove that.

01:23:27.862 --> 01:23:30.781
When I went back, I saw officers
interviewing the neighbors.

01:23:32.009 --> 01:23:34.622
I didn't know how they found it
or what happened,

01:23:34.813 --> 01:23:36.695
but I never went
back there again.

01:23:39.268 --> 01:23:41.649
You're not okay, Cooper.

01:23:42.800 --> 01:23:44.182
I know that.

01:23:46.603 --> 01:23:48.446
We could have managed.

01:23:54.859 --> 01:23:58.046
Let's finish this, at least.

01:23:58.506 --> 01:24:00.197
Riley's pie.

01:24:01.463 --> 01:24:03.576
It was supposed to be
a celebration.

01:24:14.673 --> 01:24:16.247
Sit back down.

01:24:17.783 --> 01:24:19.397
Just for a last moment.

01:24:23.352 --> 01:24:25.004
No knives, please.

01:24:31.186 --> 01:24:34.104
[dishes clattering]

01:24:38.981 --> 01:24:40.863
[Rachel breathing shakily]

01:24:59.948 --> 01:25:01.714
This won't delay it much,
I'm afraid. [sighs]

01:25:02.522 --> 01:25:04.288
I'll eat this in five bites.

01:25:04.825 --> 01:25:05.978
I know.

01:25:14.002 --> 01:25:17.459
I feel such rage
toward you, Rachel.

01:25:18.265 --> 01:25:20.378
I've never felt this before.

01:25:23.028 --> 01:25:26.252
That's different. That's...

01:25:28.326 --> 01:25:30.708
...about being seen by them.

01:25:32.359 --> 01:25:35.929
At the end,
the way they look at me...

01:25:37.812 --> 01:25:39.271
...it strangely gives me peace.

01:25:40.499 --> 01:25:42.459
There's almost no darkness
in it at all.

01:25:42.650 --> 01:25:45.875
[fork scraping against plate]

01:25:47.373 --> 01:25:50.600
This is pure anger.

01:25:52.250 --> 01:25:54.016
It's so unfamiliar.

01:25:54.247 --> 01:25:57.780
It's like it's eating me
from the inside.

01:25:58.509 --> 01:26:01.198
I feel out of control.

01:26:02.542 --> 01:26:04.500
[fork scrapes against plate]

01:26:08.379 --> 01:26:11.220
But it's why I'm angry
that's amazing.

01:26:12.410 --> 01:26:14.676
It's because I won't see
Riley and Logan again.

01:26:17.134 --> 01:26:18.479
Because of you...

01:26:20.167 --> 01:26:21.973
I won't get to see them grow up.

01:26:24.430 --> 01:26:26.389
[voice wavering]
And that's overwhelming me.

01:26:35.797 --> 01:26:36.757
Because...

01:26:38.370 --> 01:26:39.944
it's gonna end in... [sniffles]

01:26:40.137 --> 01:26:41.787
...the average way.

01:26:44.091 --> 01:26:46.357
A headline of murder-suicide.

01:26:47.356 --> 01:26:49.891
[breathes shakily]

01:26:50.082 --> 01:26:52.617
[kettle whistling]

01:27:11.242 --> 01:27:12.855
You found my bag.

01:27:13.008 --> 01:27:15.234
[whistling continues]

01:27:15.388 --> 01:27:16.732
[Rachel] You left it in the car.

01:27:19.843 --> 01:27:22.378
The police were too busy
trying to track you down.

01:27:26.102 --> 01:27:29.175
Is that what you used on them?

01:27:30.557 --> 01:27:32.285
Just to calm them.

01:27:34.474 --> 01:27:36.855
[whistling continues]

01:27:45.379 --> 01:27:48.375
[breathing heavily]

01:27:48.567 --> 01:27:52.216
[Cooper's mom] It's amazing
that you are angry, son.

01:28:04.004 --> 01:28:06.423
I thought I was pretending.

01:28:09.149 --> 01:28:10.647
But I wasn't.

01:28:12.913 --> 01:28:16.100
[Cooper's mom]
Not all of you is a monster.

01:28:18.827 --> 01:28:20.017
Not all.

01:28:22.284 --> 01:28:23.780
You're my son.

01:28:24.703 --> 01:28:26.162
And this is who you are.

01:28:27.236 --> 01:28:28.620
End of story.

01:28:32.036 --> 01:28:33.573
[knife scrapes]

01:28:33.804 --> 01:28:35.340
It's good it's over.

01:28:37.067 --> 01:28:38.257
It's good you're...

01:28:39.910 --> 01:28:41.484
...you're stopping the monster.

01:28:43.211 --> 01:28:45.938
Let see me you one last time.

01:28:59.763 --> 01:29:01.605
I accept you.

01:29:05.138 --> 01:29:06.790
Come closer.

01:29:08.480 --> 01:29:12.397
[breathing rapidly]

01:29:14.815 --> 01:29:15.775
[exhales]

01:29:17.926 --> 01:29:19.001
[kettle whistling]

01:29:19.231 --> 01:29:20.038
[electricity crackling]

01:29:20.191 --> 01:29:22.151
[screaming]

01:29:23.878 --> 01:29:25.645
[Cooper grunts]

01:29:25.798 --> 01:29:26.988
[Cooper roars]

01:29:28.332 --> 01:29:29.792
[Cooper growling]

01:29:29.945 --> 01:29:31.521
[electricity crackles]

01:29:31.751 --> 01:29:33.517
[straining, grunting]

01:29:33.708 --> 01:29:35.591
[panting]

01:29:36.819 --> 01:29:38.355
[stun gun whines]

01:29:38.548 --> 01:29:41.081
-[electricity crackling]
-[Cooper screaming]

01:29:42.426 --> 01:29:46.151
[screaming, straining]

01:30:07.502 --> 01:30:09.422
[kettle whistling]

01:30:11.380 --> 01:30:12.570
[whistling stops]

01:30:15.029 --> 01:30:17.179
We'll get your kids
back to you soon.

01:30:23.054 --> 01:30:26.127
[indistinct radio chatter]

01:30:38.913 --> 01:30:40.374
[rifle cocks]

01:30:40.527 --> 01:30:43.100
-[distant sirens]
-[helicopter whirring overhead]

01:30:43.676 --> 01:30:45.403
[Cooper]
Please, give me a second.

01:30:45.596 --> 01:30:47.400
[indistinct radio chatter
continues]

01:30:47.554 --> 01:30:48.974
[Rachel] Don't shoot him!

01:31:14.895 --> 01:31:18.044
[radio chatter continues]

01:31:27.222 --> 01:31:29.219
-Oh, my God.
-[Dr. Grant] Let her go!

01:31:30.332 --> 01:31:31.409
[Riley gasps]

01:31:34.019 --> 01:31:35.939
[Riley sobbing]

01:31:38.129 --> 01:31:39.588
[Rachel] Riley.

01:31:39.779 --> 01:31:41.738
[Riley continues sobbing]

01:31:54.333 --> 01:31:56.176
[shackles jingling]

01:32:07.543 --> 01:32:09.463
-[sirens wailing]
-[engines starting]

01:32:11.537 --> 01:32:13.496
[indistinct radio chatter]

01:32:28.011 --> 01:32:30.853
[indistinct radio chatter]

01:32:31.045 --> 01:32:32.120
[exhales forcefully]

01:32:32.350 --> 01:32:34.309
[engine starts]

01:32:35.614 --> 01:32:38.417
[sirens blaring]

01:32:38.571 --> 01:32:41.643
[helicopter blades whirring]

01:33:33.792 --> 01:33:35.481
[lock clicks open]

01:33:35.674 --> 01:33:38.515
["Pieces" by Lady Raven playing]

01:33:41.933 --> 01:33:46.272
[cackling]

01:33:50.612 --> 01:33:52.416
[lock clicks open]

01:33:52.608 --> 01:33:53.722
[chains clatter]

01:33:53.915 --> 01:33:56.448
[laughs, exhales]

01:33:56.641 --> 01:33:58.484
["Pieces"
by Lady Raven continues]

01:34:11.579 --> 01:34:13.192
[suspenseful music sting on tv]

01:34:13.383 --> 01:34:15.611
[newscaster]
<i> Breaking news tonight</i>
<i> out of Malvern, Pennsylvania.</i>

01:34:15.765 --> 01:34:17.416
<i>After a seven year long manhunt,</i>

01:34:17.646 --> 01:34:20.949
<i> the identity of the Butcher</i>
<i> has finally been revealed.</i>

01:34:22.063 --> 01:34:24.443
<i> Cooper Abbott,</i>
<i>a local fireman and family man,</i>

01:34:24.636 --> 01:34:26.094
<i> has been arrested.</i>

01:34:26.248 --> 01:34:28.706
<i> Here is a picture</i>
<i> of him at a local event.</i>

01:34:32.276 --> 01:34:34.926
[astonished stammering]

01:34:35.080 --> 01:34:36.809
That's Cooper!

01:34:37.845 --> 01:34:39.497
Oh!

01:34:39.689 --> 01:34:43.221
I helped him! I helped him!

01:34:44.257 --> 01:34:46.370
I ain't talking to nobody
at work no more!

01:34:46.600 --> 01:34:48.290
I ain't talking to nobody!

01:34:48.520 --> 01:34:50.440
Nobody! Kadesia!

01:34:50.594 --> 01:34:53.014
["Pieces" by Lady Raven resumes]

01:36:47.870 --> 01:36:50.827
["Liar" by Lady Raven playing]

